  "full_text": "An update for NetworkManager is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 10.\n\nNetworkManager is a system network service that manages network devices and connections, attempting to keep active network connectivity when available. Its capabilities include managing Ethernet, wireless, mobile broadband (WWAN), and PPPoE devices, as well as providing VPN integration with a variety of different VPN services.Bug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s): adding a VF configuration resets and re-configures all other VFs [rhel-10.1.z] (JIRA:RHEL-113956)  NetworkManager removes unrelated OVS ports [rhel-10.1.z] (JIRA:RHEL-121106)"
